    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "As discuessed in https://github.com/neovim/nvim-lspconfig/pull/4140#issuecomment-3426270993 with @justinmk, it would be great to support `vim.lsp.enable(name, false)` to support automatically escalating to a force shutdown after a certain amount of time, similar to on vim exit.\n\nI am able to implement this behavior myself and submit a PR, but I just wanted to quickly double check that this behavior is desired in neovim before I start working on it.",
